cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a compressed relaying scheme using physical-layer network coding and analyzes the compression rate and block error rate. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper focuses on two-way relay networks and improving network throughput. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possibility as the paper deals with correlated sources and their transmission. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possibility as the paper may involve multimedia data transmission in the two-way relay network. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still a possibility as the paper may discuss the security implications of the proposed scheme.
